<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go below • go under</xh5><p> <i>go below</i>—(Nautical) go to the lower (underwater) levels in a ship: Nora and I <u>went below</u> to our bunks to make our beds and settle in before the ship left the channel.</p><p><i>go under—</i>1. <i>(of a person or ship)</i> go below the surface of the sea: Our boat <u>went under</u> in no time at all. Some time later the submarine approached us, spraying machine gun tracer bullets.... 2. <i>(of a business)</i> fail: A few weeks before the company <u>went under</u> he checked to see if his pension was safe. 3. lose consciousness under the action of anesthesia, etc.: No one trained in administering anesthesia was dedicated to that task alone in his operating room as she <u>went under</u>.</p><p> <i>See also: come down / go down.</i></p> </entry>
